answers.body_markdown:
Use `disabled` instead of `readonly`. `readonly` only affects the editable text value of a field - whereas a checkbox has a _state_ not an editable value.

You don&#39;t actually need any specific Thymeleaf variables for this. You can just use the following plain HTML in your Thymeleaf template:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; id=&quot;randomId&quot; disabled checked&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

---


If you do want to use Thymeleaf expressions, you can use this:

```html
&lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; id=&quot;randomId&quot; th:disabled=&quot;${true}&quot; th:checked=&quot;${true}&quot;&gt;
```

These are Thymeleaf [boolean attributes](https://www.thymeleaf.org/doc/tutorials/3.0/usingthymeleaf#fixed-value-boolean-attributes).

I would just use plain HTML.

